{"parse":{"title":"desk","pageid":63657,"redirects":[],"wikitext":"==English==\n[[Image:Hermann Hesse Desk Museum Gaienhofen.jpeg|thumb|250px|A [[typewriter]] on a desk]]\n\n===Etymology===\nFrom {{inh|en|enm|deske}}, {{m|enm|desque}}, from {{der|en|la-med|desca}}, modified from {{der|en|roa-oit|desco}}, from {{der|en|la|discus}}. {{doublet|en|dais|disc|discus|dish|disk|diskos}}. See also {{der|en|de|Tisch}}, \"table\".\n\n===Pronunciation===\n* {{IPA|en|/dɛsk/|a=RP,GA}}\n* {{audio|en|En-us-desk.ogg|a=GA}}\n* {{rhymes|en|ɛsk|s=1}}\n\n===Noun===\n{{en-noun}}\n{{wp}}\n\n# A [[table]], [[frame]], or [[case]], in past centuries usually with a sloping top but now usually with a flat top, for the use of [[writer]]s and [[reader]]s. It often has a [[drawer]] or [[repository]] underneath.\n#: {{ux|en|She organized her notes neatly on her '''desk''' before starting the project.}}\n#: {{ux|en|The '''desk''' was cluttered with papers and books, making it hard to concentrate.}}\n#: {{ux|en|He sat at his '''desk''' for hours, trying to finish the report.}}\n#* {{RQ:Maxwell Mirror and the Lamp|chapter=5|passage=Here, in the transept and choir, where the service was being held, one was conscious every moment of an increasing brightness; colours glowing vividly beneath the circular chandeliers, and the rows of small lights on the choristers' '''desks''' flashed and sparkled in front of the boys' faces, deep linen collars, and red neckbands.}}\n# A reading table or [[lectern]] to support the book from which the [[liturgical]] [[service]] is read, differing from the [[pulpit]] from which the [[sermon]] is [[preach]]ed; also (especially in the United States), a pulpit. Hence, used symbolically for the clerical profession.\n# A [[department]] tasked with a particular topic or focus in certain types of businesses, such as newspapers and financial trading firms.\n#: {{ux|en|the city '''desk''', the sports '''desk'''}}\n#: {{ux|en|the options '''desk''', the equities '''desk'''}}\n# {{ellipsis of|en|mixing desk}}.\n#* {{quote-text|en|year=2009|author=Rick Snoman|title=Dance Music Manual: Tools, Toys and Techniques|page=69\n|passage=Each aux out is connected to an effects unit and the signal is then returned into the '''desk'''.}}\n# A [[station]] for a string player in an orchestra, consisting of a chair and a music stand, or a row of such stations.\n#: {{ux|en|The first four '''desks''' of cellos play separate parts, making a lush, Impressionist harmony.}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=2003|author=Sheila M. Nelson|title=The Violin and Viola: History, Structure, Techniques|url=https://www.google.co.uk/books/edition/The_Violin_and_Viola/NhVQAwAAQBAJ?hl=en&gbpv=1&dq=first-desk+violinist&pg=PA158&printsec=frontcover|page=158|passage={{...}}at best a competent viola player occupies a first '''desk''', so that he may play the occasional solos for that instrument; but I have even seen this function performed by the leaderof the first violins.}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=2006|author=Gabriel Banat|title=The Chevalier de Saint-Georges: Virtuoso of the Sword and the Bow|url=https://www.google.co.uk/books/edition/The_Chevalier_de_Saint_Georges/Yy9JgZQQ9XQC?hl=en&gbpv=1&dq=first-desk+violinist&pg=PA270&printsec=frontcover|page=270|passage=First '''desk''': Lalance, chevalier de, composer; Meslay, Masson de, President of the exchequer, amateur; Blasius, Pierre, the elder, professor of music; Second '''desk''':{{...}}}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=2014|author=Reuben Hersh|title=Peter Lax, Mathematician|url=https://www.google.co.uk/books/edition/Peter_Lax_Mathematician/ammxBgAAQBAJ?hl=en&gbpv=1&dq=first-desk+violinist&pg=PA46&printsec=frontcover|page=46|passage=Lori performed for years with the American Symphony Orchestra under Leopold Stokowski as a first-'''desk''' violinist. (She says that Stokowski was not a Russian but an Englishman named Stokes. His Russian accent varied a lot.)}}\n\n====Hypernyms====\n* {{l|en|furniture}}\n\n====Coordinate terms====\n* {{l|en|chair}}\n\n====Derived terms====\n{{col|en|al desko|circulation desk|deskband|deskbook|secretary desk|deskbound|deskercise|deskfast|deskful|desklamp|desklet|desklike|deskman|deskmate|deskphone|deskscape|deskside|deskspace|desktop|deskward|deskworker|headdesk|infodesk|newsdesk\n|cash desk|deskband|deskbook|Carlton House desk|concierge desk|deskbound|deskercise|deskfast| double desk|partners desk|deskful|desklet|desklike|deskman|deskmate|deskphone|deskscape|deskside|deskspace|desktop|deskward|deskworker|headdesk|infodesk|newsdesk| desk fan|key desk|desk job|desk organizer|desk work,deskwork|front desk|information desk|mixing desk|reception desk|Resolute desk|standing desk|cashier's desk|checkout desk|city desk|copy desk|desk caddy|desk chair|desk check|desk dictionary|desk drop|desk jockey|desk lamp|desk murderer|desk organiser|desk pad|desk pilot|desk potato|desk rage|desk rejection|desk sergeant|desk tidy|fly a desk|front-desk|help desk|help-desk|hobby desk|hot desk|hot-desk|kneehole desk|lap desk|litany desk|news desk|picture desk|roll-top desk| Governor Winthrop desk|Winthrop desk||rolltop desk|teacher's desk|telephone desk|writing desk|desk drawer|desk blotter|desk calendar|desk killer|music desk|deskie}}\n\n====Descendants====\n* {{desc|tpi|des}}\n* {{desc|bor=1|ga|deasc}}\n* {{desc|bor=1|cy|desg}}\n\n====Translations====\n{{trans-top|table for writing and reading}}\n* Afrikaans: {{t+|af|lessenaar}}\n* Altai:\n*: Southern Altai: {{t|alt|стол}}, {{t|alt|парта}}\n* Arabic: {{t+|ar|مَكْتَب|m}}, {{t|ar|مِنْضَدَة|f}}\n* Aragonese: {{t|an|escritorio|m}}, {{qualifier|school desk}} {{t|an|pupitre|m}}\n* Armenian: {{t+|hy|գրասեղան}}\n* Basque: {{t|eu|idazmahai}}\n* Belarusian: {{t|be|пісьмо́вы стол|m}}, {{t+|be|стол|m}}, {{t|be|па́рта|f}} {{qualifier|school}}\n* Bengali: {{t+|bn|ডেস্ক|tr=ḍesk}}, {{t+|bn|মেজ}}\n* Bulgarian: {{t+|bg|бюро́|n}}, {{t+|bg|писа́лище|n}}\n* Catalan: {{t+|ca|escriptori|m}}, {{qualifier|in a classroom}} {{t+|ca|pupitre|m}}\n* Chinese:\n*: Mandarin: {{t+|cmn|書桌|tr=shūzhuō}}, {{t|cmn|寫字檯//寫字枱//寫字臺//寫字台}}\n* Czech: {{t+|cs|psací stůl|m}}\n* Danish: {{t+|da|skrivebord|n}}\n* Dutch: {{t+|nl|bureau|n}}, {{t+|nl|schrijftafel|f}}, {{t+|nl|lessenaar|f}}\n* Esperanto: {{t|eo|skribotablo}}, {{t|eo|skribtablo}}\n* Estonian: {{t|et|kirjutuslaud}}, {{t|et|koolipink}}, {{t|et|pult}}\n* Faroese: {{t|fo|skriviborð|n}}\n* Finnish: {{t+|fi|työpöytä}}, {{t+|fi|kirjoituspöytä}}\n* French: {{t+|fr|bureau|m}}, {{qualifier|school desk}} {{t+|fr|pupitre|m}}\n* Frisian:\n*: West Frisian: {{t|fy|buro|n}}\n* Galician: {{t+|gl|escritorio|m}}, {{t+|gl|pupitre|m}}\n* Georgian: {{t|ka|საწერი მაგიდა}}\n* German: {{t+|de|Schreibtisch|m}}\n* Greek: {{t+|el|γραφείο|n}}\n* Hawaiian: {{t|haw|pākaukau}}\n* Hebrew: {{t+|he|מִכְתָּבָה|f|tr=makhtevá}}, {{t+|he|שולחן כתיבה|m|tr=shulkhán ktivá|alt=שֻׁלְחַן כְּתִיבָה \\ שולחן כתיבה}}\n* Hindi: {{t+|hi|मेज़|f}}\n* Hungarian: {{t+|hu|íróasztal}}, {{t+|hu|dolgozóasztal}}, {{q|in school}} {{t+|hu|pad}}, {{t+|hu|iskolapad}}\n* Icelandic: {{t+|is|skrifborð|n}}\n* Ingrian: {{t|izh|kans}}, {{t|izh|lauta}}, {{t|izh|pöytä}}\n* Irish: {{t|ga|deasc}}\n* Italian: {{t+|it|scrivania|f}}\n* Japanese: {{t+|ja|机|tr=つくえ, tsukue}}\n* Korean: {{t+|ko|책상(冊床)}}\n* Kumyk: {{t|kum|стол}}\n* Kurdish:\n*: Central Kurdish: {{t+|ckb|مێز}}\n*: Northern Kurdish: {{t+|kmr|doşk|m}}, {{t+|kmr|mase|f}}, {{t+|kmr|mêze|f}}\n* Kyrgyz: {{t+|ky|стол}}\n* Lao: {{t+|lo|ໂຕະ}}\n* Latin: {{t|la|mensa scriptoria|f}}\n* Latvian: {{t|lv|rakstāmgalds|m}}\n* Luhya: {{t|luy|litesiki}}\n* Macedonian: {{t|mk|биро́|n}}\n* Malay: {{t|ms|meja tulis}}\n* Māori: {{t|mi|tēpu tuhi}}\n* Mongolian:\n*: Cyrillic: {{t+|mn|ширээ}}\n*: Mongolian script: {{t|mn|ᠰᠢᠷᠡᠭᠡ}}\n* Navajo: {{t|nv|bikááʼ naʼanishí}}\n* Norman: {{t|nrf|êcritouaithe|m}}\n* Norwegian:\n*: Bokmål: {{t|nb|pult|m}}, {{t+|nb|skrivebord|n}}\n*: Nynorsk: {{t|nn|skrivebord|n}}\n* Persian:\n*: Dari: {{t+|prs|میز}}, {{t|prs|میزِ تَحْرِیر}}\n*: Iranian Persian: {{t+|fa-ira|میز}}, {{t|fa-ira|میزِ تَحْریر}}\n* Polish: {{t+|pl|biurko|n}}\n* Portuguese: {{t+|pt|escrivaninha|f}}, {{t+|pt|carteira|f}} {{q|especially the type used in schools}}\n* Romanian: {{t+|ro|birou|n}}\n* Russian: {{t+|ru|пи́сьменный стол|m}}, {{t+|ru|стол|m}}, {{t+|ru|па́рта|f}} {{qualifier|school}}, {{t+|ru|бюро́|n}}, {{t+|ru|рабо́чий стол|m}}\n* Scottish Gaelic: {{t|gd|bòrd-sgrìobhaidh|m}}, {{t|gd|deasg|m}}\n* Serbo-Croatian:\n*: Cyrillic: {{t|sh|писаћи сто|m}}, {{t|sh|радни сто|m}}\n*: Latin: {{t|sh|pisaći sto|m}}, {{t|sh|radni sto|m}}\n* Slovak: {{t|sk|písací stôl|m}}, {{t|sk|pracovný stôl|m}}\n* Slovene: {{t+|sl|pisalna miza|f}}, {{t|sl|delovna miza|f}}\n* Spanish: {{t+|es|escritorio|m}}, {{qualifier|school desk}} {{t+|es|pupitre|m}}, {{t+|es|carpeta|f}} {{qualifier|school desk|Peru|Cuba}}, {{t|es|mesabanco|f}} {{qualifier|student desk|Mexico}}, {{t|es|secreter|m}}, {{t+|es|escribanía|f}}\n* Swahili: {{t+|sw|dawati}}\n* Swedish: {{qualifier|school desk}} {{t+|sv|skolbänk|c}}, {{qualifier|otherwise}} {{t+|sv|skrivbord|n}}\n* Thai: {{t+|th|โต๊ะ}}, {{t|th|[[โต๊ะ]][[ทำงาน]]|tr=dtó tam-ngaan}}\n* Turkish: {{t+|tr|masa}}, {{t+|tr|sıra}}, {{t+|tr|çalışma masası}}, {{t|tr|çalışak}}, {{t+|tr|büro}}\n*: Ottoman Turkish: {{t|ota|رحله|tr=rahle}}\n* Ukrainian: {{t|uk|письмо́вий стіл|m}}, {{t+|uk|стіл|m}}, {{t|uk|па́рта|f}} {{qualifier|school}}\n* Urdu: {{t|ur|میز تَحْرِیر|f}}, {{t|ur|میز|f}}\n* Uyghur: {{t|ug|جوزا}}, {{t|ug|پارتا}} {{qualifier|school}}\n* Uzbek: {{t+|uz|qabul}}\n* Vietnamese: {{t+|vi|bàn}}\n* Volapük: {{t+|vo|püpit}}\n* Walloon: {{t+|wa|buro|m}}, {{t|wa|scribanc|m}}, {{t+|wa|perpite|m}} {{qualifier|school desk}}\n* Welsh: {{t+|cy|desg|f}}, {{t|cy|desgiau|f-p}}\n* Yiddish: {{t|yi|שרײַבטיש|m}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n{{trans-see|lectern}}\n\n{{trans-top|team in a news outlet specialized on a topic}}\n* Danish: {{t|da|rubrik}}, {{t|da|stationær redaktion}}\n* Dutch: {{t|nl|deelredactie}}, {{t|nl|deskredactie}}\n* French: {{t+|fr|rubrique|f}}\n* German: {{t+|de|Ressort|f}}\n* Portuguese: {{t|pt|editoria|f}}\n* Spanish: {{t+|es|sección|f}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n<!-- moved here from a trans section on escritorio#Spanish -->\n{{checktrans-top}}\n* Interlingua: {{t-check|ia|scriptorio}}\n{{trans-bottom}}\n\n===Verb===\n{{en-verb}}\n\n# {{lb|en|transitive}} To shut up, as in a desk; to [[treasure]]. {{rfex|en}}\n# {{lb|en|transitive}} To [[equip]] with a desk or desks.\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=1775 |title=The will of king Henry vii [ed. by T. Astle.]. |author=Henry VII (King of England) |page= 6|ISBN=|passage=But also that the said Chapell be '''desked''', and the windowes of our said Chapell be glased, with Stores, Ymagies, Armes, Bagies ami Cognossaunts, as is by us redily divised, and in picture delivered to the Priour of Saunt Bartilmews besid Smythfel, maistre of the works of our said Chapell;}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=1914 |title=The Builder - Volume 106 |author=|page=528 |ISBN=|passage=The teaching accommodation is to be as follows ;— Senior Mixed Department—Five rooms of equal area, four of which are each to be '''desked''' for forty scholars and one to be '''desked''' for thirty-two scholars}}\n#* {{quote-book|en|year=2001 |title=A Collection of Nodding Off Stories |author=Bonnie M Gulan |page=64 |ISBN=|passage=Each row of '''desked''' benches was stepped up a step from the other until the top row of '''desked''' benches seemed to hit its high ceiling.}}\n# {{lb|en|transitive|journalism}} To [[reject]] (an [[article]] submitted to a [[newspaper]] or [[academic]] [[journal]] etc.) on initial [[receipt]], without [[review]]ing it further.\n\n===Anagrams===\n* {{anagrams|en|a=deks|KEDs|deks|keds|sked}}\n\n{{C|en|Furniture}}\n\n==Middle English==\n\n===Adjective===\n{{head|enm|adjective|altform=1}} \n\n# {{alt form|enm|dosk}}"}}